==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Satirize
<hw>Sat"ir*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Satirized</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Satirizing</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>satiriser</ets>.]</ety> <def>To make the object of satire; to
attack with satire; to censure with keenness or severe
sarcasm.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is as hard to <qex>satirize</qex> well a man of distinguished
vices, as to praise well a man of distinguished virtues.</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Satisfaction</ent>⟦br⟧
